71static const char *proposal_names[PROPOSAL_MAX] = {
72 "KEX algorithms",
73 "host key algorithms",
74 "ciphers ctos",
75 "ciphers stoc",
76 "MACs ctos",
77 "MACs stoc",
78 "compression ctos",

84struct kexalg {
85 const char *name;
86 u_int type;
87 int ec_nid;
88 int hash_alg;
89};
90static const struct kexalg kexalgs[] = {
91#ifdef WITH_OPENSSL
92 { KEX_DH1, KEX_DH_GRP1_SHA1, 0, SSH_DIGEST_SHA1 },
93 { KEX_DH14_SHA1, KEX_DH_GRP14_SHA1, 0, SSH_DIGEST_SHA1 },
94 { KEX_DH14_SHA256, KEX_DH_GRP14_SHA256, 0, SSH_DIGEST_SHA256 },
95 { KEX_DH16_SHA512, KEX_DH_GRP16_SHA512, 0, SSH_DIGEST_SHA512 },
96 { KEX_DH18_SHA512, KEX_DH_GRP18_SHA512, 0, SSH_DIGEST_SHA512 },
97 { KEX_DHGEX_SHA1, KEX_DH_GEX_SHA1, 0, SSH_DIGEST_SHA1 },
98 { KEX_DHGEX_SHA256, KEX_DH_GEX_SHA256, 0, SSH_DIGEST_SHA256 },
99 { KEX_ECDH_SHA2_NISTP256, KEX_ECDH_SHA2,
100 NID_X9_62_prime256v1, SSH_DIGEST_SHA256 },
101 { KEX_ECDH_SHA2_NISTP384, KEX_ECDH_SHA2, NID_secp384r1,
102 SSH_DIGEST_SHA384 },
103 { KEX_ECDH_SHA2_NISTP521, KEX_ECDH_SHA2, NID_secp521r1,
104 SSH_DIGEST_SHA512 },
105#endif
106 { KEX_CURVE25519_SHA256, KEX_C25519_SHA256, 0, SSH_DIGEST_SHA256 },
107 { KEX_CURVE25519_SHA256_OLD, KEX_C25519_SHA256, 0, SSH_DIGEST_SHA256 },
108 { KEX_SNTRUP4591761X25519_SHA512, KEX_KEM_SNTRUP4591761X25519_SHA512, 0,
109 SSH_DIGEST_SHA512 },
110 { NULL, (u_int)-1, -1, -1},
111};
112
113char *
114kex_alg_list(char sep)
115{
116 char *ret = NULL, *tmp;
117 size_t nlen, rlen = 0;
118 const struct kexalg *k;
119
120 for (k = kexalgs; k->name != NULL; k++) {
121 if (ret != NULL)
122 ret[rlen++] = sep;
123 nlen = strlen(k->name);
124 if ((tmp = realloc(ret, rlen + nlen + 2)) == NULL) {
125 free(ret);
126 return NULL;
127 }
128 ret = tmp;
129 memcpy(ret + rlen, k->name, nlen + 1);
130 rlen += nlen;
131 }
132 return ret;
133}
134
135static const struct kexalg *
136kex_alg_by_name(const char *name)
137{
138 const struct kexalg *k;
139
140 for (k = kexalgs; k->name != NULL; k++) {
141 if (strcmp(k->name, name) == 0)
142 return k;
143 }
144 return NULL;
145}
146
147/* Validate KEX method name list */
148int
149kex_names_valid(const char *names)
150{
151 char *s, *cp, *p;
152
153 if (names == NULL || strcmp(names, "") == 0)
154 return 0;
155 if ((s = cp = strdup(names)) == NULL)
156 return 0;
157 for ((p = strsep(&cp, ",")); p && *p != '\0';
158 (p = strsep(&cp, ","))) {
159 if (kex_alg_by_name(p) == NULL) {
160 error("Unsupported KEX algorithm \"%.100s\"", p);
161 free(s);
162 return 0;
163 }
164 }
165 debug3("kex names ok: [%s]", names);
166 free(s);
167 return 1;
168}
169
170/*
171 * Concatenate algorithm names, avoiding duplicates in the process.
172 * Caller must free returned string.
173 */
174char *
175kex_names_cat(const char *a, const char *b)
176{
177 char *ret = NULL, *tmp = NULL, *cp, *p, *m;
178 size_t len;
179
180 if (a == NULL || *a == '\0')
181 return strdup(b);
182 if (b == NULL || *b == '\0')
183 return strdup(a);
184 if (strlen(b) > 1024*1024)
185 return NULL;
186 len = strlen(a) + strlen(b) + 2;
187 if ((tmp = cp = strdup(b)) == NULL ||
188 (ret = calloc(1, len)) == NULL) {
189 free(tmp);
190 return NULL;
191 }
192 strlcpy(ret, a, len);
193 for ((p = strsep(&cp, ",")); p && *p != '\0'; (p = strsep(&cp, ","))) {
194 if ((m = match_list(ret, p, NULL)) != NULL) {
195 free(m);
196 continue; /* Algorithm already present */
197 }
198 if (strlcat(ret, ",", len) >= len ||
199 strlcat(ret, p, len) >= len) {
200 free(tmp);
201 free(ret);
202 return NULL; /* Shouldn't happen */
203 }
204 }
205 free(tmp);
206 return ret;
207}
208
209/*
210 * Assemble a list of algorithms from a default list and a string from a
211 * configuration file. The user-provided string may begin with '+' to
212 * indicate that it should be appended to the default or '-' that the
213 * specified names should be removed.
214 */
215int
216kex_assemble_names(char **listp, const char *def, const char *all)
217{
218 char *cp, *tmp, *patterns;
219 char *list = NULL, *ret = NULL, *matching = NULL, *opatterns = NULL;
220 int r = SSH_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR;
221
222 if (listp == NULL || *listp == NULL || **listp == '\0') {
223 if ((*listp = strdup(def)) == NULL)
224 return SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
225 return 0;
226 }
227
228 list = *listp;
229 *listp = NULL;
230 if (*list == '+') {
231 /* Append names to default list */
232 if ((tmp = kex_names_cat(def, list + 1)) == NULL) {
233 r = SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
234 goto fail;
235 }
236 free(list);
237 list = tmp;
238 } else if (*list == '-') {
239 /* Remove names from default list */
240 if ((*listp = match_filter_blacklist(def, list + 1)) == NULL) {
241 r = SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
242 goto fail;
243 }
244 free(list);
245 /* filtering has already been done */
246 return 0;
247 } else {
248 /* Explicit list, overrides default - just use "list" as is */
249 }
250
251 /*
252 * The supplied names may be a pattern-list. For the -list case,
253 * the patterns are applied above. For the +list and explicit list
254 * cases we need to do it now.
255 */
256 ret = NULL;
257 if ((patterns = opatterns = strdup(list)) == NULL) {
258 r = SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
259 goto fail;
260 }
261 /* Apply positive (i.e. non-negated) patterns from the list */
262 while ((cp = strsep(&patterns, ",")) != NULL) {
263 if (*cp == '!') {
264 /* negated matches are not supported here */
265 r = SSH_ERR_INVALID_ARGUMENT;
266 goto fail;
267 }
268 free(matching);
269 if ((matching = match_filter_whitelist(all, cp)) == NULL) {
270 r = SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
271 goto fail;
272 }
273 if ((tmp = kex_names_cat(ret, matching)) == NULL) {
274 r = SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
275 goto fail;
276 }
277 free(ret);
278 ret = tmp;
279 }
280 if (ret == NULL || *ret == '\0') {
281 /* An empty name-list is an error */
282 /* XXX better error code? */
283 r = SSH_ERR_INVALID_ARGUMENT;
284 goto fail;
285 }
286
287 /* success */
288 *listp = ret;
289 ret = NULL;
290 r = 0;
291
292 fail:
293 free(matching);
294 free(opatterns);
295 free(list);
296 free(ret);
297 return r;
298}
299
300/* put algorithm proposal into buffer */
301int
302kex_prop2buf(struct sshbuf *b, const char *proposal[PROPOSAL_MAX])
303{
304 u_int i;
305 int r;
306
307 sshbuf_reset(b);
308
309 /*
310 * add a dummy cookie, the cookie will be overwritten by
311 * kex_send_kexinit(), each time a kexinit is set
312 */
313 for (i = 0; i < KEX_COOKIE_LEN; i++) {
314 if ((r = sshbuf_put_u8(b, 0)) != 0)
315 return r;
316 }
317 for (i = 0; i < PROPOSAL_MAX; i++) {
318 if ((r = sshbuf_put_cstring(b, proposal[i])) != 0)
319 return r;
320 }
321 if ((r = sshbuf_put_u8(b, 0)) != 0 || /* first_kex_packet_follows */
322 (r = sshbuf_put_u32(b, 0)) != 0) /* uint32 reserved */
323 return r;
324 return 0;
325}
326
327/* parse buffer and return algorithm proposal */
328int
329kex_buf2prop(struct sshbuf *raw, int *first_kex_follows, char ***propp)
330{
331 struct sshbuf *b = NULL;
332 u_char v;
333 u_int i;
334 char **proposal = NULL;
335 int r;
336
337 *propp = NULL;
338 if ((proposal = calloc(PROPOSAL_MAX, sizeof(char *))) == NULL)
339 return SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
340 if ((b = sshbuf_fromb(raw)) == NULL) {
341 r = SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
342 goto out;
343 }
344 if ((r = sshbuf_consume(b, KEX_COOKIE_LEN)) != 0) /* skip cookie */
345 goto out;
346 /* extract kex init proposal strings */
347 for (i = 0; i < PROPOSAL_MAX; i++) {
348 if ((r = sshbuf_get_cstring(b, &(proposal[i]), NULL)) != 0)
349 goto out;
350 debug2("%s: %s", proposal_names[i], proposal[i]);
351 }
352 /* first kex follows / reserved */
353 if ((r = sshbuf_get_u8(b, &v)) != 0 || /* first_kex_follows */
354 (r = sshbuf_get_u32(b, &i)) != 0) /* reserved */
355 goto out;
356 if (first_kex_follows != NULL)
357 *first_kex_follows = v;
358 debug2("first_kex_follows %d ", v);
359 debug2("reserved %u ", i);
360 r = 0;
361 *propp = proposal;
362 out:
363 if (r != 0 && proposal != NULL)
364 kex_prop_free(proposal);
365 sshbuf_free(b);
366 return r;
367}
368
369void
370kex_prop_free(char **proposal)
371{
372 u_int i;
373
374 if (proposal == NULL)
375 return;
376 for (i = 0; i < PROPOSAL_MAX; i++)
377 free(proposal[i]);
378 free(proposal);
379}

381/* ARGSUSED */
382static int
383kex_protocol_error(int type, u_int32_t seq, struct ssh *ssh)
384{
385 int r;
386
387 error("kex protocol error: type %d seq %u", type, seq);
388 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_UNIMPLEMENTED)) != 0 ||
389 (r = sshpkt_put_u32(ssh, seq)) != 0 ||
390 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
391 return r;
392 return 0;
393}
394
395static void
396kex_reset_dispatch(struct ssh *ssh)
397{
398 ssh_dispatch_range(ssh, SSH2_MSG_TRANSPORT_MIN,
399 SSH2_MSG_TRANSPORT_MAX, &kex_protocol_error);
400}
401
402static int
403kex_send_ext_info(struct ssh *ssh)
404{
405 int r;
406 char *algs;
407
408 if ((algs = sshkey_alg_list(0, 1, 1, ',')) == NULL)
409 return SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
410 /* XXX filter algs list by allowed pubkey/hostbased types */
411 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_EXT_INFO)) != 0 ||
412 (r = sshpkt_put_u32(ssh, 1)) != 0 ||
413 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, "server-sig-algs")) != 0 ||
414 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, algs)) != 0 ||
415 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
416 goto out;
417 /* success */
418 r = 0;
419 out:
420 free(algs);
421 return r;
422}
423
424int
425kex_send_newkeys(struct ssh *ssh)
426{
427 int r;
428
429 kex_reset_dispatch(ssh);
430 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_NEWKEYS)) != 0 ||
431 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
432 return r;
433 debug("SSH2_MSG_NEWKEYS sent");
434 debug("expecting SSH2_MSG_NEWKEYS");
435 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_NEWKEYS, &kex_input_newkeys);
436 if (ssh->kex->ext_info_c)
437 if ((r = kex_send_ext_info(ssh)) != 0)
438 return r;
439 return 0;
440}
441
442int
443kex_input_ext_info(int type, u_int32_t seq, struct ssh *ssh)
444{
445 struct kex *kex = ssh->kex;
446 u_int32_t i, ninfo;
447 char *name;
448 u_char *val;
449 size_t vlen;
450 int r;
451
452 debug("SSH2_MSG_EXT_INFO received");
453 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_EXT_INFO, &kex_protocol_error);
454 if ((r = sshpkt_get_u32(ssh, &ninfo)) != 0)
455 return r;
456 if (ninfo > 1024) {
457 fatal("%s: too many %u fields", __func__, ninfo);
458 return SSH_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR;
459 }
460 for (i = 0; i < ninfo; i++) {
461 if ((r = sshpkt_get_cstring(ssh, &name, NULL)) != 0)
462 return r;
463 if ((r = sshpkt_get_string(ssh, &val, &vlen)) != 0) {
464 free(name);
465 return r;
466 }
467 if (strcmp(name, "server-sig-algs") == 0) {
468 char *cval = (void *)val;
469 /* Ensure no \0 lurking in value */
470 if (memchr(val, '\0', vlen) != NULL) {
471 error("%s: nul byte in %s", __func__, name);
472 return SSH_ERR_INVALID_FORMAT;
473 }
474 debug("%s: %s=<%s>", __func__, name, cval);
475 kex->server_sig_algs = cval;
476 val = NULL;
477 } else
478 debug("%s: %s (unrecognised)", __func__, name);
479 free(name);
480 free(val);
481 }
482 return sshpkt_get_end(ssh);
483}
484
485static int
486kex_input_newkeys(int type, u_int32_t seq, struct ssh *ssh)
487{
488 struct kex *kex = ssh->kex;
489 int r;
490
491 debug("SSH2_MSG_NEWKEYS received");
492 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_NEWKEYS, &kex_protocol_error);
493 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_KEXINIT, &kex_input_kexinit);
494 if ((r = sshpkt_get_end(ssh)) != 0)
495 return r;
496 if ((r = ssh_set_newkeys(ssh, MODE_IN)) != 0)
497 return r;
498 kex->done = 1;
499 kex->flags &= ~KEX_INITIAL;
500 sshbuf_reset(kex->peer);
501 /* sshbuf_reset(kex->my); */
502 kex->flags &= ~KEX_INIT_SENT;
503 free(kex->name);
504 kex->name = NULL;
505 return 0;
506}
507
508int
509kex_send_kexinit(struct ssh *ssh)
510{
511 u_char *cookie;
512 struct kex *kex = ssh->kex;
513 int r;
514
515 if (kex == NULL)
516 return SSH_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR;
517 if (kex->flags & KEX_INIT_SENT)
518 return 0;
519 kex->done = 0;
520
521 /* generate a random cookie */
522 if (sshbuf_len(kex->my) < KEX_COOKIE_LEN)
523 return SSH_ERR_INVALID_FORMAT;
524 if ((cookie = sshbuf_mutable_ptr(kex->my)) == NULL)
525 return SSH_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR;
526 arc4random_buf(cookie, KEX_COOKIE_LEN);
527
528 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_KEXINIT)) != 0 ||
529 (r = sshpkt_putb(ssh, kex->my)) != 0 ||
530 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
531 return r;
532 debug("SSH2_MSG_KEXINIT sent");
533 kex->flags |= KEX_INIT_SENT;
534 return 0;
535}
536
537/* ARGSUSED */
538int
539kex_input_kexinit(int type, u_int32_t seq, struct ssh *ssh)
540{
541 struct kex *kex = ssh->kex;
542 const u_char *ptr;
543 u_int i;
544 size_t dlen;
545 int r;
546
547 debug("SSH2_MSG_KEXINIT received");
548 if (kex == NULL)
549 return SSH_ERR_INVALID_ARGUMENT;
550
551 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_KEXINIT, NULL);
552 ptr = sshpkt_ptr(ssh, &dlen);
553 if ((r = sshbuf_put(kex->peer, ptr, dlen)) != 0)
554 return r;
555
556 /* discard packet */
557 for (i = 0; i < KEX_COOKIE_LEN; i++)
558 if ((r = sshpkt_get_u8(ssh, NULL)) != 0)
559 return r;
560 for (i = 0; i < PROPOSAL_MAX; i++)
561 if ((r = sshpkt_get_string(ssh, NULL, NULL)) != 0)
562 return r;
563 /*
564 * XXX RFC4253 sec 7: "each side MAY guess" - currently no supported
565 * KEX method has the server move first, but a server might be using
566 * a custom method or one that we otherwise don't support. We should
567 * be prepared to remember first_kex_follows here so we can eat a
568 * packet later.
569 * XXX2 - RFC4253 is kind of ambiguous on what first_kex_follows means
570 * for cases where the server *doesn't* go first. I guess we should
571 * ignore it when it is set for these cases, which is what we do now.
572 */
573 if ((r = sshpkt_get_u8(ssh, NULL)) != 0 || /* first_kex_follows */
574 (r = sshpkt_get_u32(ssh, NULL)) != 0 || /* reserved */
575 (r = sshpkt_get_end(ssh)) != 0)
576 return r;
577
578 if (!(kex->flags & KEX_INIT_SENT))
579 if ((r = kex_send_kexinit(ssh)) != 0)
580 return r;
581 if ((r = kex_choose_conf(ssh)) != 0)
582 return r;
583
584 if (kex->kex_type < KEX_MAX && kex->kex[kex->kex_type] != NULL)
585 return (kex->kex[kex->kex_type])(ssh);
586
587 return SSH_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR;
588}
589
590struct kex *
591kex_new(void)
592{
593 struct kex *kex;
594
595 if ((kex = calloc(1, sizeof(*kex))) == NULL ||
596 (kex->peer = sshbuf_new()) == NULL ||
597 (kex->my = sshbuf_new()) == NULL ||
598 (kex->client_version = sshbuf_new()) == NULL ||
599 (kex->server_version = sshbuf_new()) == NULL) {
600 kex_free(kex);
601 return NULL;
602 }
603 return kex;
604}
605
606void
607kex_free_newkeys(struct newkeys *newkeys)
608{
609 if (newkeys == NULL)
610 return;
611 if (newkeys->enc.key) {
612 explicit_bzero(newkeys->enc.key, newkeys->enc.key_len);
613 free(newkeys->enc.key);
614 newkeys->enc.key = NULL;
615 }
616 if (newkeys->enc.iv) {
617 explicit_bzero(newkeys->enc.iv, newkeys->enc.iv_len);
618 free(newkeys->enc.iv);
619 newkeys->enc.iv = NULL;
620 }
621 free(newkeys->enc.name);
622 explicit_bzero(&newkeys->enc, sizeof(newkeys->enc));
623 free(newkeys->comp.name);
624 explicit_bzero(&newkeys->comp, sizeof(newkeys->comp));
625 mac_clear(&newkeys->mac);
626 if (newkeys->mac.key) {
627 explicit_bzero(newkeys->mac.key, newkeys->mac.key_len);
628 free(newkeys->mac.key);
629 newkeys->mac.key = NULL;
630 }
631 free(newkeys->mac.name);
632 explicit_bzero(&newkeys->mac, sizeof(newkeys->mac));
633 explicit_bzero(newkeys, sizeof(*newkeys));
634 free(newkeys);
635}
636
637void
638kex_free(struct kex *kex)
639{
640 u_int mode;
641
642 if (kex == NULL)
643 return;
644
645#ifdef WITH_OPENSSL
646 DH_free(kex->dh);
647 EC_KEY_free(kex->ec_client_key);
648#endif
649 for (mode = 0; mode < MODE_MAX; mode++) {
650 kex_free_newkeys(kex->newkeys[mode]);
651 kex->newkeys[mode] = NULL;
652 }
653 sshbuf_free(kex->peer);
654 sshbuf_free(kex->my);
655 sshbuf_free(kex->client_version);
656 sshbuf_free(kex->server_version);
657 sshbuf_free(kex->client_pub);
658 free(kex->session_id);
659 free(kex->failed_choice);
660 free(kex->hostkey_alg);
661 free(kex->name);
662 free(kex);
663}
664
665int
666kex_ready(struct ssh *ssh, const char *proposal[PROPOSAL_MAX])
667{
668 int r;
669
670 if ((r = kex_prop2buf(ssh->kex->my, proposal)) != 0)
671 return r;
672 ssh->kex->flags = KEX_INITIAL;
673 kex_reset_dispatch(ssh);
674 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_KEXINIT, &kex_input_kexinit);
675 return 0;
676}
677
678int
679kex_setup(struct ssh *ssh, const char *proposal[PROPOSAL_MAX])
680{
681 int r;
682
683 if ((r = kex_ready(ssh, proposal)) != 0)
684 return r;
685 if ((r = kex_send_kexinit(ssh)) != 0) { /* we start */
686 kex_free(ssh->kex);
687 ssh->kex = NULL;
688 return r;
689 }
690 return 0;
691}
692
693/*
694 * Request key re-exchange, returns 0 on success or a ssherr.h error
695 * code otherwise. Must not be called if KEX is incomplete or in-progress.
696 */
697int
698kex_start_rekex(struct ssh *ssh)
699{
700 if (ssh->kex == NULL) {
701 error("%s: no kex", __func__);
702 return SSH_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR;
703 }
704 if (ssh->kex->done == 0) {
705 error("%s: requested twice", __func__);
706 return SSH_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR;
707 }
708 ssh->kex->done = 0;
709 return kex_send_kexinit(ssh);
710}
711
712static int
713choose_enc(struct sshenc *enc, char *client, char *server)
714{
715 char *name = match_list(client, server, NULL);
716
717 if (name == NULL)
718 return SSH_ERR_NO_CIPHER_ALG_MATCH;
719 if ((enc->cipher = cipher_by_name(name)) == NULL) {
720 free(name);
721 return SSH_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR;
722 }
723 enc->name = name;
724 enc->enabled = 0;
725 enc->iv = NULL;
726 enc->iv_len = cipher_ivlen(enc->cipher);
727 enc->key = NULL;
728 enc->key_len = cipher_keylen(enc->cipher);
729 enc->block_size = cipher_blocksize(enc->cipher);
730 return 0;
731}
732
733static int
734choose_mac(struct ssh *ssh, struct sshmac *mac, char *client, char *server)
735{
736 char *name = match_list(client, server, NULL);
737
738 if (name == NULL)
739 return SSH_ERR_NO_MAC_ALG_MATCH;
740 if (mac_setup(mac, name) < 0) {
741 free(name);
742 return SSH_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR;
743 }
744 mac->name = name;
745 mac->key = NULL;
746 mac->enabled = 0;
747 return 0;
748}
749
750static int
751choose_comp(struct sshcomp *comp, char *client, char *server)
752{
753 char *name = match_list(client, server, NULL);
754
755 if (name == NULL)
756 return SSH_ERR_NO_COMPRESS_ALG_MATCH;
757 if (strcmp(name, "zlib@openssh.com") == 0) {
758 comp->type = COMP_DELAYED;
759 } else if (strcmp(name, "zlib") == 0) {
760 comp->type = COMP_ZLIB;
761 } else if (strcmp(name, "none") == 0) {
762 comp->type = COMP_NONE;
763 } else {
764 free(name);
765 return SSH_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR;
766 }
767 comp->name = name;
768 return 0;
769}
770
771static int
772choose_kex(struct kex *k, char *client, char *server)
773{
774 const struct kexalg *kexalg;
775
776 k->name = match_list(client, server, NULL);
777
778 debug("kex: algorithm: %s", k->name ? k->name : "(no match)");
779 if (k->name == NULL)
780 return SSH_ERR_NO_KEX_ALG_MATCH;
781 if ((kexalg = kex_alg_by_name(k->name)) == NULL)
782 return SSH_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR;
783 k->kex_type = kexalg->type;
784 k->hash_alg = kexalg->hash_alg;
785 k->ec_nid = kexalg->ec_nid;
786 return 0;
787}
788
789static int
790choose_hostkeyalg(struct kex *k, char *client, char *server)
791{
792 k->hostkey_alg = match_list(client, server, NULL);
793
794 debug("kex: host key algorithm: %s",
795 k->hostkey_alg ? k->hostkey_alg : "(no match)");
796 if (k->hostkey_alg == NULL)
797 return SSH_ERR_NO_HOSTKEY_ALG_MATCH;
798 k->hostkey_type = sshkey_type_from_name(k->hostkey_alg);
799 if (k->hostkey_type == KEY_UNSPEC)
800 return SSH_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR;
801 k->hostkey_nid = sshkey_ecdsa_nid_from_name(k->hostkey_alg);
802 return 0;
803}
804
805static int
806proposals_match(char *my[PROPOSAL_MAX], char *peer[PROPOSAL_MAX])
807{
808 static int check[] = {
809 PROPOSAL_KEX_ALGS, PROPOSAL_SERVER_HOST_KEY_ALGS, -1
810 };
811 int *idx;
812 char *p;
813
814 for (idx = &check[0]; *idx != -1; idx++) {
815 if ((p = strchr(my[*idx], ',')) != NULL)
816 *p = '\0';
817 if ((p = strchr(peer[*idx], ',')) != NULL)
818 *p = '\0';
819 if (strcmp(my[*idx], peer[*idx]) != 0) {
820 debug2("proposal mismatch: my %s peer %s",
821 my[*idx], peer[*idx]);
822 return (0);
823 }
824 }
825 debug2("proposals match");
826 return (1);
827}
828
829static int
830kex_choose_conf(struct ssh *ssh)
831{
832 struct kex *kex = ssh->kex;
833 struct newkeys *newkeys;
834 char **my = NULL, **peer = NULL;
835 char **cprop, **sprop;
836 int nenc, nmac, ncomp;
837 u_int mode, ctos, need, dh_need, authlen;
838 int log_flag = 0;
839 int r, first_kex_follows;
840
841 debug2("local %s KEXINIT proposal", kex->server ? "server" : "client");
842 if ((r = kex_buf2prop(kex->my, NULL, &my)) != 0)
843 goto out;
844 debug2("peer %s KEXINIT proposal", kex->server ? "client" : "server");
845 if ((r = kex_buf2prop(kex->peer, &first_kex_follows, &peer)) != 0)
846 goto out;
847
848 if (kex->server) {
849 cprop=peer;
850 sprop=my;
851 } else {
852 cprop=my;
853 sprop=peer;
854 }
855
856 /* Check whether client supports ext_info_c */
857 if (kex->server && (kex->flags & KEX_INITIAL)) {
858 char *ext;
859
860 ext = match_list("ext-info-c", peer[PROPOSAL_KEX_ALGS], NULL);
861 kex->ext_info_c = (ext != NULL);
862 free(ext);
863 }
864
865 /* Algorithm Negotiation */
866 if ((r = choose_kex(kex, cprop[PROPOSAL_KEX_ALGS],
867 sprop[PROPOSAL_KEX_ALGS])) != 0) {
868 kex->failed_choice = peer[PROPOSAL_KEX_ALGS];
869 peer[PROPOSAL_KEX_ALGS] = NULL;
870 goto out;
871 }
872 if ((r = choose_hostkeyalg(kex, cprop[PROPOSAL_SERVER_HOST_KEY_ALGS],
873 sprop[PROPOSAL_SERVER_HOST_KEY_ALGS])) != 0) {
874 kex->failed_choice = peer[PROPOSAL_SERVER_HOST_KEY_ALGS];
875 peer[PROPOSAL_SERVER_HOST_KEY_ALGS] = NULL;
876 goto out;
877 }
878 for (mode = 0; mode < MODE_MAX; mode++) {
879 if ((newkeys = calloc(1, sizeof(*newkeys))) == NULL) {
880 r = SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
881 goto out;
882 }
883 kex->newkeys[mode] = newkeys;
884 ctos = (!kex->server && mode == MODE_OUT) ||
885 (kex->server && mode == MODE_IN);
886 nenc = ctos ? PROPOSAL_ENC_ALGS_CTOS : PROPOSAL_ENC_ALGS_STOC;
887 nmac = ctos ? PROPOSAL_MAC_ALGS_CTOS : PROPOSAL_MAC_ALGS_STOC;
888 ncomp = ctos ? PROPOSAL_COMP_ALGS_CTOS : PROPOSAL_COMP_ALGS_STOC;
889 if ((r = choose_enc(&newkeys->enc, cprop[nenc],
890 sprop[nenc])) != 0) {
891 kex->failed_choice = peer[nenc];
892 peer[nenc] = NULL;
893 goto out;
894 }
895 authlen = cipher_authlen(newkeys->enc.cipher);
896 /* ignore mac for authenticated encryption */
897 if (authlen == 0 &&
898 (r = choose_mac(ssh, &newkeys->mac, cprop[nmac],
899 sprop[nmac])) != 0) {
900 kex->failed_choice = peer[nmac];
901 peer[nmac] = NULL;
902 goto out;
903 }
904 if ((r = choose_comp(&newkeys->comp, cprop[ncomp],
905 sprop[ncomp])) != 0) {
906 kex->failed_choice = peer[ncomp];
907 peer[ncomp] = NULL;
908 goto out;
909 }
910 debug("REQUESTED ENC.NAME is '%s'", newkeys->enc.name);
911 if (strcmp(newkeys->enc.name, "none") == 0) {
912 int auth_flag;
913
914 auth_flag = ssh_packet_authentication_state(ssh);
915 debug("Requesting NONE. Authflag is %d", auth_flag);
916 if (auth_flag == 1) {
917 debug("None requested post authentication.");
918 } else {
919 fatal("Pre-authentication none cipher requests are not allowed.");
920 }
921 }
922 debug("kex: %s cipher: %s MAC: %s compression: %s",
923 ctos ? "client->server" : "server->client",
924 newkeys->enc.name,
925 authlen == 0 ? newkeys->mac.name : "<implicit>",
926 newkeys->comp.name);
927 /* client starts withctos = 0 && log flag = 0 and no log*/
928 /* 2nd client pass ctos=1 and flag = 1 so no log*/
929 /* server starts with ctos =1 && log_flag = 0 so log */
930 /* 2nd sever pass ctos = 1 && log flag = 1 so no log*/
931 /* -cjr*/
932 if (ctos && !log_flag) {
933 logit("SSH: Server;Ltype: Kex;Remote: %s-%d;Enc: %s;MAC: %s;Comp: %s",
934 ssh_remote_ipaddr(ssh),
935 ssh_remote_port(ssh),
936 newkeys->enc.name,
937 newkeys->mac.name,
938 newkeys->comp.name);
939 }
940 log_flag = 1;
941 }
942 need = dh_need = 0;
943 for (mode = 0; mode < MODE_MAX; mode++) {
944 newkeys = kex->newkeys[mode];
945 need = MAXIMUM(need, newkeys->enc.key_len);
946 need = MAXIMUM(need, newkeys->enc.block_size);
947 need = MAXIMUM(need, newkeys->enc.iv_len);
948 need = MAXIMUM(need, newkeys->mac.key_len);
949 dh_need = MAXIMUM(dh_need, cipher_seclen(newkeys->enc.cipher));
950 dh_need = MAXIMUM(dh_need, newkeys->enc.block_size);
951 dh_need = MAXIMUM(dh_need, newkeys->enc.iv_len);
952 dh_need = MAXIMUM(dh_need, newkeys->mac.key_len);
953 }
954 /* XXX need runden? */
955 kex->we_need = need;
956 kex->dh_need = dh_need;
957
958 /* ignore the next message if the proposals do not match */
959 if (first_kex_follows && !proposals_match(my, peer))
960 ssh->dispatch_skip_packets = 1;
961 r = 0;
962 out:
963 kex_prop_free(my);
964 kex_prop_free(peer);
965 return r;
966}
967
968static int
969derive_key(struct ssh *ssh, int id, u_int need, u_char *hash, u_int hashlen,
970 const struct sshbuf *shared_secret, u_char **keyp)
971{
972 struct kex *kex = ssh->kex;
973 struct ssh_digest_ctx *hashctx = NULL;
974 char c = id;
975 u_int have;
976 size_t mdsz;
977 u_char *digest;
978 int r;
979
980 if ((mdsz = ssh_digest_bytes(kex->hash_alg)) == 0)
981 return SSH_ERR_INVALID_ARGUMENT;
982 if ((digest = calloc(1, ROUNDUP(need, mdsz))) == NULL) {
983 r = SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
984 goto out;
985 }
986
987 /* K1 = HASH(K || H || "A" || session_id) */
988 if ((hashctx = ssh_digest_start(kex->hash_alg)) == NULL ||
989 ssh_digest_update_buffer(hashctx, shared_secret) != 0 ||
990 ssh_digest_update(hashctx, hash, hashlen) != 0 ||
991 ssh_digest_update(hashctx, &c, 1) != 0 ||
992 ssh_digest_update(hashctx, kex->session_id,
993 kex->session_id_len) != 0 ||
994 ssh_digest_final(hashctx, digest, mdsz) != 0) {
995 r = SSH_ERR_LIBCRYPTO_ERROR;
996 goto out;
997 }
998 ssh_digest_free(hashctx);
999 hashctx = NULL;
1000
1001 /*
1002 * expand key:
1003 * Kn = HASH(K || H || K1 || K2 || ... || Kn-1)
1004 * Key = K1 || K2 || ... || Kn
1005 */
1006 for (have = mdsz; need > have; have += mdsz) {
1007 if ((hashctx = ssh_digest_start(kex->hash_alg)) == NULL ||
1008 ssh_digest_update_buffer(hashctx, shared_secret) != 0 ||
1009 ssh_digest_update(hashctx, hash, hashlen) != 0 ||
1010 ssh_digest_update(hashctx, digest, have) != 0 ||
1011 ssh_digest_final(hashctx, digest + have, mdsz) != 0) {
1012 r = SSH_ERR_LIBCRYPTO_ERROR;
1013 goto out;
1014 }
1015 ssh_digest_free(hashctx);
1016 hashctx = NULL;
1017 }
1018#ifdef DEBUG_KEX
1019 fprintf(stderr, "key '%c'== ", c);
1020 dump_digest("key", digest, need);
1021#endif
1022 *keyp = digest;
1023 digest = NULL;
1024 r = 0;
1025 out:
1026 free(digest);
1027 ssh_digest_free(hashctx);
1028 return r;
1029}
1030
1031#define NKEYS 6
1032int
1033kex_derive_keys(struct ssh *ssh, u_char *hash, u_int hashlen,
1034 const struct sshbuf *shared_secret)
1035{
1036 struct kex *kex = ssh->kex;
1037 u_char *keys[NKEYS];
1038 u_int i, j, mode, ctos;
1039 int r;
1040
1041 /* save initial hash as session id */
1042 if (kex->session_id == NULL) {
1043 kex->session_id_len = hashlen;
1044 kex->session_id = malloc(kex->session_id_len);
1045 if (kex->session_id == NULL)
1046 return SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
1047 memcpy(kex->session_id, hash, kex->session_id_len);
1048 }
1049 for (i = 0; i < NKEYS; i++) {
1050 if ((r = derive_key(ssh, 'A'+i, kex->we_need, hash, hashlen,
1051 shared_secret, &keys[i])) != 0) {
1052 for (j = 0; j < i; j++)
1053 free(keys[j]);
1054 return r;
1055 }
1056 }
1057 for (mode = 0; mode < MODE_MAX; mode++) {
1058 ctos = (!kex->server && mode == MODE_OUT) ||
1059 (kex->server && mode == MODE_IN);
1060 kex->newkeys[mode]->enc.iv = keys[ctos ? 0 : 1];
1061 kex->newkeys[mode]->enc.key = keys[ctos ? 2 : 3];
1062 kex->newkeys[mode]->mac.key = keys[ctos ? 4 : 5];
1063 }
1064 return 0;
1065}
1066
1067int
1068kex_load_hostkey(struct ssh *ssh, struct sshkey **prvp, struct sshkey **pubp)
1069{
1070 struct kex *kex = ssh->kex;
1071
1072 *pubp = NULL;
1073 *prvp = NULL;
1074 if (kex->load_host_public_key == NULL ||
1075 kex->load_host_private_key == NULL)
1076 return SSH_ERR_INVALID_ARGUMENT;
1077 *pubp = kex->load_host_public_key(kex->hostkey_type,
1078 kex->hostkey_nid, ssh);
1079 *prvp = kex->load_host_private_key(kex->hostkey_type,
1080 kex->hostkey_nid, ssh);
1081 if (*pubp == NULL)
1082 return SSH_ERR_NO_HOSTKEY_LOADED;
1083 return 0;
1084}
1085
1086int
1087kex_verify_host_key(struct ssh *ssh, struct sshkey *server_host_key)
1088{
1089 struct kex *kex = ssh->kex;
1090
1091 if (kex->verify_host_key == NULL)
1092 return SSH_ERR_INVALID_ARGUMENT;
1093 if (server_host_key->type != kex->hostkey_type ||
1094 (kex->hostkey_type == KEY_ECDSA &&
1095 server_host_key->ecdsa_nid != kex->hostkey_nid))
1096 return SSH_ERR_KEY_TYPE_MISMATCH;
1097 if (kex->verify_host_key(server_host_key, ssh) == -1)
1098 return SSH_ERR_SIGNATURE_INVALID;
1099 return 0;
1100}

1111/*
1112 * Send a plaintext error message to the peer, suffixed by \r\n.
1113 * Only used during banner exchange, and there only for the server.
1114 */
1115static void
1116send_error(struct ssh *ssh, const char *msg)
1117{
1118 const char *crnl = "\r\n";
1119
1120 if (!ssh->kex->server)
1121 return;
1122
1123 if (atomicio(vwrite, ssh_packet_get_connection_out(ssh),
1124 __UNCONST(msg), strlen(msg)) != strlen(msg) ||
1125 atomicio(vwrite, ssh_packet_get_connection_out(ssh),
1126 __UNCONST(crnl), strlen(crnl)) != strlen(crnl))
1127 error("%s: write: %.100s", __func__, strerror(errno));
1128}
1129
1130/*
1131 * Sends our identification string and waits for the peer's. Will block for
1132 * up to timeout_ms (or indefinitely if timeout_ms <= 0).
1133 * Returns on 0 success or a ssherr.h code on failure.
1134 */
1135int
1136kex_exchange_identification(struct ssh *ssh, int timeout_ms,
1137 const char *version_addendum)
1138{
1139 int remote_major, remote_minor, mismatch;
1140 size_t len, i, n;
1141 int r, expect_nl;
1142 u_char c;
1143 struct sshbuf *our_version = ssh->kex->server ?
1144 ssh->kex->server_version : ssh->kex->client_version;
1145 struct sshbuf *peer_version = ssh->kex->server ?
1146 ssh->kex->client_version : ssh->kex->server_version;
1147 char *our_version_string = NULL, *peer_version_string = NULL;
1148 char *cp, *remote_version = NULL;
1149
1150 /* Prepare and send our banner */
1151 sshbuf_reset(our_version);
1152 if (version_addendum != NULL && *version_addendum == '\0')
1153 version_addendum = NULL;
1154 if ((r = sshbuf_putf(our_version, "SSH-%d.%d-%.100s%s%s\r\n",
1155 PROTOCOL_MAJOR_2, PROTOCOL_MINOR_2, SSH_VERSION,
1156 version_addendum == NULL ? "" : " ",
1157 version_addendum == NULL ? "" : version_addendum)) != 0) {
1158 error("%s: sshbuf_putf: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
1159 goto out;
1160 }
1161
1162 if (atomicio(vwrite, ssh_packet_get_connection_out(ssh),
1163 sshbuf_mutable_ptr(our_version),
1164 sshbuf_len(our_version)) != sshbuf_len(our_version)) {
1165 error("%s: write: %.100s", __func__, strerror(errno));
1166 r = SSH_ERR_SYSTEM_ERROR;
1167 goto out;
1168 }
1169 if ((r = sshbuf_consume_end(our_version, 2)) != 0) { /* trim \r\n */
1170 error("%s: sshbuf_consume_end: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
1171 goto out;
1172 }
1173 our_version_string = sshbuf_dup_string(our_version);
1174 if (our_version_string == NULL) {
1175 error("%s: sshbuf_dup_string failed", __func__);
1176 r = SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
1177 goto out;
1178 }
1179 debug("Local version string %.100s", our_version_string);
1180
1181 /* Read other side's version identification. */
1182 for (n = 0; ; n++) {
1183 if (n >= SSH_MAX_PRE_BANNER_LINES) {
1184 send_error(ssh, "No SSH identification string "
1185 "received.");
1186 error("%s: No SSH version received in first %u lines "
1187 "from server", __func__, SSH_MAX_PRE_BANNER_LINES);
1188 r = SSH_ERR_INVALID_FORMAT;
1189 goto out;
1190 }
1191 sshbuf_reset(peer_version);
1192 expect_nl = 0;
1193 for (i = 0; ; i++) {
1194 if (timeout_ms > 0) {
1195 r = waitrfd(ssh_packet_get_connection_in(ssh),
1196 &timeout_ms);
1197 if (r == -1 && errno == ETIMEDOUT) {
1198 send_error(ssh, "Timed out waiting "
1199 "for SSH identification string.");
1200 error("Connection timed out during "
1201 "banner exchange");
1202 r = SSH_ERR_CONN_TIMEOUT;
1203 goto out;
1204 } else if (r == -1) {
1205 error("%s: %s",
1206 __func__, strerror(errno));
1207 r = SSH_ERR_SYSTEM_ERROR;
1208 goto out;
1209 }
1210 }
1211
1212 len = atomicio(read, ssh_packet_get_connection_in(ssh),
1213 &c, 1);
1214 if (len != 1 && errno == EPIPE) {
1215 error("%s: Connection closed by remote host",
1216 __func__);
1217 r = SSH_ERR_CONN_CLOSED;
1218 goto out;
1219 } else if (len != 1) {
1220 error("%s: read: %.100s",
1221 __func__, strerror(errno));
1222 r = SSH_ERR_SYSTEM_ERROR;
1223 goto out;
1224 }
1225 if (c == '\r') {
1226 expect_nl = 1;
1227 continue;
1228 }
1229 if (c == '\n')
1230 break;
1231 if (c == '\0' || expect_nl) {
1232 error("%s: banner line contains invalid "
1233 "characters", __func__);
1234 goto invalid;
1235 }
1236 if ((r = sshbuf_put_u8(peer_version, c)) != 0) {
1237 error("%s: sshbuf_put: %s",
1238 __func__, ssh_err(r));
1239 goto out;
1240 }
1241 if (sshbuf_len(peer_version) > SSH_MAX_BANNER_LEN) {
1242 error("%s: banner line too long", __func__);
1243 goto invalid;
1244 }
1245 }
1246 /* Is this an actual protocol banner? */
1247 if (sshbuf_len(peer_version) > 4 &&
1248 memcmp(sshbuf_ptr(peer_version), "SSH-", 4) == 0)
1249 break;
1250 /* If not, then just log the line and continue */
1251 if ((cp = sshbuf_dup_string(peer_version)) == NULL) {
1252 error("%s: sshbuf_dup_string failed", __func__);
1253 r = SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
1254 goto out;
1255 }
1256 /* Do not accept lines before the SSH ident from a client */
1257 if (ssh->kex->server) {
1258 error("%s: client sent invalid protocol identifier "
1259 "\"%.256s\"", __func__, cp);
1260 free(cp);
1261 goto invalid;
1262 }
1263 debug("%s: banner line %zu: %s", __func__, n, cp);
1264 free(cp);
1265 }
1266 peer_version_string = sshbuf_dup_string(peer_version);
1267 if (peer_version_string == NULL)
1268 error("%s: sshbuf_dup_string failed", __func__);
1269 /* XXX must be same size for sscanf */
1270 if ((remote_version = calloc(1, sshbuf_len(peer_version))) == NULL) {
1271 error("%s: calloc failed", __func__);
1272 r = SSH_ERR_ALLOC_FAIL;
1273 goto out;
1274 }
1275
1276 /*
1277 * Check that the versions match. In future this might accept
1278 * several versions and set appropriate flags to handle them.
1279 */
1280 if (sscanf(peer_version_string, "SSH-%d.%d-%[^\n]\n",
1281 &remote_major, &remote_minor, remote_version) != 3) {
1282 error("Bad remote protocol version identification: '%.100s'",
1283 peer_version_string);
1284 invalid:
1285 send_error(ssh, "Invalid SSH identification string.");
1286 r = SSH_ERR_INVALID_FORMAT;
1287 goto out;
1288 }
1289 debug("Remote protocol version %d.%d, remote software version %.100s",
1290 remote_major, remote_minor, remote_version);
1291 ssh->compat = compat_datafellows(remote_version);
1292
1293 mismatch = 0;
1294 switch (remote_major) {
1295 case 2:
1296 break;
1297 case 1:
1298 if (remote_minor != 99)
1299 mismatch = 1;
1300 break;
1301 default:
1302 mismatch = 1;
1303 break;
1304 }
1305 if (mismatch) {
1306 error("Protocol major versions differ: %d vs. %d",
1307 PROTOCOL_MAJOR_2, remote_major);
1308 send_error(ssh, "Protocol major versions differ.");
1309 r = SSH_ERR_NO_PROTOCOL_VERSION;
1310 goto out;
1311 }
1312
1313 if (ssh->kex->server && (ssh->compat & SSH_BUG_PROBE) != 0) {
1314 logit("probed from %s port %d with %s. Don't panic.",
1315 ssh_remote_ipaddr(ssh), ssh_remote_port(ssh),
1316 peer_version_string);
1317 r = SSH_ERR_CONN_CLOSED; /* XXX */
1318 goto out;
1319 }
1320 if (ssh->kex->server && (ssh->compat & SSH_BUG_SCANNER) != 0) {
1321 logit("scanned from %s port %d with %s. Don't panic.",
1322 ssh_remote_ipaddr(ssh), ssh_remote_port(ssh),
1323 peer_version_string);
1324 r = SSH_ERR_CONN_CLOSED; /* XXX */
1325 goto out;
1326 }
1327 if ((ssh->compat & SSH_BUG_RSASIGMD5) != 0) {
1328 logit("Remote version \"%.100s\" uses unsafe RSA signature "
1329 "scheme; disabling use of RSA keys", remote_version);
1330 }
1331 /* success */
1332 r = 0;
1333 out:
1334 free(our_version_string);
1335 free(peer_version_string);
1336 free(remote_version);
1337 return r;
1338}
